1️⃣ Security Architecture Overview

Goal: Prevent users from generating redemption codes from home or spoofed GPS locations.

Flow:

Member selects location.

App retrieves device GPS coordinates.

App verifies user is within 200 meters of wash station.

Coordinates + timestamp are cryptographically signed.

Sent as required header to GraphQL generateRedemptionCode.

Backend validates:

Distance <= 200m

Timestamp < 60s old

Not reused

Device integrity check passed

Only then issue QR code.

This prevents:

Desktop spoofing

GPS tampering

Replay attacks

Remote code farming

2️⃣ Anti-Spoofing Strategy

You must assume users will try to fake location.

Therefore:

Required Layers
Layer	Purpose
GPS proximity check	Basic enforcement
Timestamp validation	Prevent replay
Device ID binding	Prevent header reuse
JWT authentication	Member validation
Server-side re-check	Never trust frontend
IP + Geo anomaly detection	Fraud scoring
Optional device integrity check	Advanced anti-spoof

Frontend check is UX.
Backend check is enforcement.

